    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Transition Panels</title>
        <para>The transition panel and reinforcing bar are fastened to the bus cowl section. A yellow adhesive sealer
            may be utilized in the installation of the transition panels. This sealer must also be removed and the areas
            cleaned prior to the installation of the new transition panel, if applicable.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the transition panel, locate the upper and lower mounting screws, 4 at the top and
                two at the bottom.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47004126" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/g47004126.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 126. Transition Panel Remove</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TRANSITION PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TRANSITION PANEL REINFORCING FLAT BAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DRIVER SIDE FRESH AIR INLET PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. REINFORCING BAR MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. LOWER TRANSITION PANEL MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. TRANSITION PANEL (DRIVERS SIDE SHOWN)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the mounting screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the vertical transition panel mounting bracket, loosen and remove the mounting
                screws.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the transition panel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure for the opposite side.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
